article.headline: Jackson State 83, Alabama State 65
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Trey Johnson scored 26 points to lead Jackson State to an 83-65 victory over Alabama State Thursday in the quarterfinals of the Southwestern Athletic Conference Tournament. Dakari Wallace scored 16 points and Charlie White had 14 for the Tigers (15-16), who will play the Southern University-Alcorn State winner Friday night. Alabama State (12-18) had won the previous meeting 93-79 in the regular-season finale. Jackson State shot 46 percent overall and made 5-of-11 3-pointers in the second half to extend a 39-27 halftime lead. Catraiva Givens had nine points and seven assists for Jackson State. Herbert Warren led Alabama State with 14 points and 10 rebounds. Akeim Claborn and Cedric Mitchell had 10 points apiece.
